Draghi Pre-Selected as ECB’s Trichet Successor, Standard Reports

-- B y   Z o e   S c h n e e w e i s s
-- 
2011-04-10T19:57:58Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-10/draghi-pre-selected-as-ecb-s-trichet-successor-standard-reports.html
Bank of  Italy  Governor  Mario Draghi 
has been pre-selected to succeed  Jean-Claude Trichet  as European
Central Bank president,  Der Standard  reported, without citing
anyone.  Germany  has passed on proposing a candidate and
alternatives to Draghi aren’t in sight, the Vienna-based
newspaper said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Zoe Schneeweiss at 
 zschneeweiss@bloomberg.net  